### Hadith 1:257

*Narrated Maimuna:*

I placed water for the bath of the Prophet. He washed his hands twice or
thrice and then poured water on his left hand and washed his private
parts. He rubbed his hands over the earth (and cleaned them), rinsed his
mouth, washed his nose by putting water in it and blowing it out, washed
his face and both forearms and then poured water over his body. Then he
withdrew from that place and washed his feet.

